  "number": 1285,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1285",
  "title": "[API] change getConfiguration signature to manipulate SearchParameters",
  "body": "Right now, the getConfiguration works on plain objects. Those plain objects are then merged into a single object.\n\nThis way of doing has several issues: \n- Its usage rely on knowing the internal structure of the `SearchParameters`\n- the merge is naive, which leads to issues\n- the user has poor control on the application of his changes\n\nBuuuut `SearchParameters` have a nice and friendly API. So what about this API:\n\n``` js\ngetConfiguration(SearchParameters, stateFromTheURL) => SearchParameters\n```\n\nWhen implementing a widget this would look like: \n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget({\n  getConfiguration: function(searchParams, url) {\n    return searchParams.addFacet('myFacet');\n  }\n});\n```\n\nBonus: in the same spirit of giving more power / responsability to the implementors, maybe it should be their responsability to merge what comes from the URL?\n",
